<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Richard S. Miller (1945–2021), who first identified these specimens as a new genus and species but never described them. Rich worked primarily on 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1101,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lycidae</taxonomicName>
but was knowledgeable about a wide range of beetles and other insects, including all other ‘cantharoids’. Rich was a close friend and colleague of MAI and a role model and source of inspiration to VSF.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1302,1328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[331,534,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis box="[331,534,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1050,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[875,993,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a dorsally unicolorous pronotum and elytra (
<figureCitation box="[527,611,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) (vs. pronotal disc in 
<taxonomicName box="[850,1013,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ballantynae">
<emphasis box="[850,869,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[881,1013,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">ballantynae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
yellow), the pronotum not constricted medially (
<figureCitation box="[263,347,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) (vs. constricted in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[566,708,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis box="[566,585,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[598,708,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the last three abdominal segments distinctly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1312,1427,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F, 1I</figureCitation>
) (vs. dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[362,459,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis box="[362,381,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[395,459,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or not distinctly yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[760,903,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis box="[760,779,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[793,903,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having ventrite 8 posteriorly entire and apically round (
<figureCitation box="[327,409,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
) (vs. notched in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[598,741,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis box="[598,617,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[631,741,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergite VIII posteriorly notched (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1246,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
) (vs. tergite VIII entire in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[251,355,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis box="[251,270,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[283,355,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[409,521,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis box="[409,521,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C. hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Description.</emphasis>
General color dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[675,776,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
), mandibles, elytral insertions, trochanters, tarsi and last three abdominal segments yellow (
<figureCitation box="[546,645,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
