<figureCitation box="[926,1012,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Abdomenal tergite VIII with distinct median notch (
<figureCitation box="[318,394,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
); ventrite 7 shallowly notched posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[880,961,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[973,1012,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">2D</figureCitation>
