<figureCitation box="[487,572,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with median lobe stout, fusiform, apically round, in ventral view bearing paired strut-like structure, divergent apically (
<figureCitation box="[811,898,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
